  "prompt": "At age 25, it is too young for marry to my girlfriend?",
  "response": "Deciding to get married is a personal choice and can vary greatly depending on individual circumstances, values, and goals. At 25, many people may feel ready to marry, while others may prefer to wait longer. Here are some factors to consider:\n\n1. **Relationship Stability**: How long have you been together? Do you have a strong foundation of mutual trust and understanding?\n\n2. **Life Goals**: Are your life goals and dreams aligned? This includes career plans, financial stability, and family aspirations.\n\n3. **Communication**: Can you openly discuss important topics like finances, children, and future plans with your girlfriend?\n\n4. **Support System**: Do your family and friends support your decision, and do you both have a healthy support system?\n\n5. **Maturity**: Do you feel emotionally mature and ready to handle the responsibilities that come with marriage?\n\nUltimately, there's no \"right\" age to get married. It\u2019s more about whether you and your girlfriend are ready for that commitment. Take the time to discuss these aspects before making a decision.",
